ies called <i>de la Hewatte</i> (1270), <i>de la hewett</i> (1301), and <i>atte Hewete</i> (1338). The name may also be topographic for someone who lived in a newly made clearing in a wood."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":12,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":85,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Hewett was born about 1370, in England. He married Mrs. Hewett after 1390, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1370–":"umbes 1370–Surnud","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","about 1370":"umbes 1370","1455":"1455","after 1390":"pärast 1390","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1390":"1390","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1370–":"noin 1370–Kuollut","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","about 1370":"noin 1370","1455":"1455","after 1390":"1390 jälkeen","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1390":"1390","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1370–":"environ 1370–Décédé","1370–Female":"1370–Décédée","1390–Male":"1390–Décédé","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","about 1370":"environ 1370","